# Expense Operating Travel Accommodation Entertainment Amount

## identifier
de7566

## type
float

## definition
This is the amount incurred on travelling, accommodation and entertainment expenses. Travelling costs are costs incurred for transportation services relating to business activities which occur away from the normal place of business. These costs are only to be included if they are incurred in connection with business activities. Accommodation expenses are those costs incurred in providing accommodation to staff when business activities occur away from the normal place of business. Entertainment expenses are the costs incurred by a business for the provision of entertainment activities.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Expense.Operating.TravelAccommodationEntertainment.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpr/bafpr2.02.06
- period=duration
